tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased HbA1c (4.0%), which may suggest recent hypoglycemia, low average glucose, or possible analytical/physiological variation. No evidence of renal, electrolyte, or metabolic disturbances. Correlate HbA1c finding with clinical context and consider repeat if clinically indicated.
